The paper discusses a spatial indexing method using relational algebra and B-Tree mechanism commonly found in relational database systems. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the database (cs.DB) and data structures (cs.DS) sub-categories. The paper also mentions queries related to spatial data search, which could fall under information retrieval (cs.IR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper includes an implementation using the USGS city and stream gauge database, which could relate to computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category.
